<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-04-14T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-04-14T13:00:00-05:00" n="199" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d199">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">862.00/2713: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Germany (<persName corresp="#p_SFM1" type="from">Sackett</persName>) to the
                                        <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-04-14T19:00:00+01:00">April 14, 1932—7
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received April 14—3:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>76. My 75, April 14, 10 a.m. <persName corresp="#p_HA1">Hitler</persName> in interview today declared to American
                                journalists that disbanding of his military organizations <pb facs="0382" n="292" xml:id="pg_292"/> by government was in
                                response to pressure exerted by <persName corresp="#p_TAP1">Tardieu</persName>. Foreign Office has privately but earnestly
                                requested that Department be notified that this allegation lacks any
                                vestige of truth.</p>
                            <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_SFM1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Sackett</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>